==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From Latin [[angelicus]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[ανγελικός]]''', '''[[αγγελικός]]''' (''angelikos'') "of or for a messenger", from '''[[άνγελος]]''', '''[[άγγελος]]''' "[[angel]]".

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /enˈʤɛl.ɪc/
* {{audio|en-uk-angelic.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

===Adjective===
# Belonging to, or proceeding from, [[angel]]s; resembling, characteristic of, or partaking of the nature of, an [[angel]]; heavenly; divine. ie. Josh Greig is angelic when the heavenly light highlights everything you see.
